parameters.description: Initial Nutrient concentration (g C m^-3), fixed from the first data point.
Initial Phytoplankton concentration (g C m^-3), fixed from the first data point.
Initial Zooplankton concentration (g C m^-3), fixed from the first data point.
Log of the maximum phytoplankton specific growth rate (V_max, day^-1). V_max = exp(log_V_max), ensuring positivity. This is the maximum rate of nutrient uptake per unit of phytoplankton.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log maximum phytoplankton growth rate per day

parameters.description: Log of the half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake (K_N, g C m^-3). K_N = exp(log_K_N). This is the nutrient concentration at which the phytoplankton growth rate is half of its maximum.
Log of the maximum zooplankton specific grazing rate (g_max, day^-1). g_max = exp(log_g_max). This is the maximum rate of phytoplankton consumption per unit of zooplankton.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log maximum zooplankton grazing rate per day

parameters.description: Log of the half-saturation constant for a Type III grazing response (K_P, g C m^-3). K_P = exp(log_K_P). This is the phytoplankton concentration at which the zooplankton grazing rate is half of its maximum. The squared terms create a sigmoidal (Type III) response, representing reduced grazing efficiency at low prey densities.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log half-saturation constant for Type III phytoplankton grazing

parameters.description: Logit of the zooplankton assimilation efficiency (beta, dimensionless). beta = invlogit(logit_beta), constraining it between 0 and 1. This represents the fraction of consumed phytoplankton that is converted into zooplankton biomass.
Log of the phytoplankton linear mortality rate (m_P, day^-1). m_P = exp(log_m_P). This represents natural death, sinking, or other losses.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log phytoplankton linear mortality rate per day

parameters.description: Log of the phytoplankton quadratic mortality rate ((g C m^-3)^-1 day^-1). m_P_sq = exp(log_m_P_sq). This term represents density-dependent losses, such as viral lysis, which are more prevalent during blooms.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log phytoplankton quadratic mortality rate per biomass

parameters.description: Log of the zooplankton linear mortality rate (m_Z, day^-1). m_Z = exp(log_m_Z). This represents the density-independent death rate of zooplankton.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log zooplankton linear mortality rate per day

parameters.description: Log of the zooplankton quadratic mortality rate (m_Z_sq, (g C m^-3)^-1 day^-1). m_Z_sq = exp(log_m_Z_sq). This term represents density-dependent losses, such as higher-order predation or disease.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log zooplankton quadratic mortality rate per biomass

parameters.description: Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model of Nutrient observations. sd_N = exp(log_sd_N).
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log standard deviation nutrient observation error

parameters.description: Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model of Phytoplankton observations. sd_P = exp(log_sd_P).
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log standard deviation phytoplankton observation error

parameters.description: Log of the standard deviation for the lognormal error model of Zooplankton observations. sd_Z = exp(log_sd_Z).
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Log standard deviation zooplankton observation error
